Etiology, symptoms, mechanism, assessment, treatment and counselling of aphasia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide theoretical knowledge about the etiology, symptoms, assessment, therapy and counselling of aphasia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) Student understands the mechanism of aphasia, describes and qualifies the symptoms. 2) Student is able to identify form of aphasia based on the description; describe the aims and methods of therapy, considering the needs of a client or patient.  3) Student is able to advise the patient's family and medical staff. 4) Student notices gaps in her theoretical knowledge during practical exercises and looks for help (asks the lector, searches corresponding scientific literature etc). 5) Student associates new theoretical knowledge with previously learned information, compares aphasia with other acquired communication disorders and with specific language impairment (SLI).
